# Ask Agent (Async)

Send the user's request to a specified CCB agent asynchronously.

## Usage

The skill signature is exactly `/ask <target> <message...>`.
Parse only once:

- `TARGET` = first token after `/ask`
- `MESSAGE` = exact raw remainder after `TARGET`

Everything after `TARGET` belongs to `MESSAGE` and must be forwarded verbatim.
This skill does not accept a sender argument.

## Execution (MANDATORY)

```powershell
Start-Process -NoNewWindow -FilePath "ccb" -ArgumentList @("ask", "$TARGET") -RedirectStandardInput (New-TemporaryFile | ForEach-Object { $MESSAGE | Set-Content $_; $_.FullName })
```

This returns only an acceptance receipt in the current turn.
The reply is not echoed into the same command stdout.
Use `ccb ask --wait "$TARGET"` only when the user explicitly wants the reply now.

## Rules

- After running the command, end your turn immediately.
- Use `--wait` only when the user explicitly wants the reply in the same turn.
- Prefer implicit sender inference; use `from system` only for deliberate overrides.

## Examples

- `/ask agent1 What is 12+12?`
- `/ask agent2 Refactor this code`
- `/ask reviewer Analyze this bug`
- `/ask worker Execute this task`

## Notes

- If it fails, report the command failure output and stop.
